about.summary: [Box Platform](https://box.dev) provides functionality to provide access to content stored within [Box](https://box.com). It provides endpoints for basic manipulation of files and folders, management of users within an enterprise, as well as more complex topics such as legal holds and retention policies.

name: box-sdk-gen
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "box-sdk-gen" %}
{% set version = "0.3.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/box-sdk-gen-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a558497661581318b9bedaa973efc4fbf1e830041b8ccd7e370342949efbe3f5

build:
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv --no-deps --no-build-isolation
  number: 0

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.8
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.8
    - cryptography >=3
    - pyjwt >=1.7.0
    - requests
    - requests-toolbelt
    - urllib3 <2

test:
  imports:
    - box_sdk_gen
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/box/box-python-sdk-gen.git
  summary: '[Box Platform](https://box.dev) provides functionality to provide access to content stored within [Box](https://box.com). It provides endpoints for basic manipulation of files and folders, management of users within an enterprise, as well as more complex topics such as legal holds and retention policies.'
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - akrherz
